{"id": "uhx1665702664428", "title": "Example: Using Database Data Paging", "breadcrumbs": ["Developing Web Applications", "Scripting in Server Pages", "Data Paging in Web Applications", "Example: Using Database Data Paging"], "url": "https://docs.rocketsoftware.com/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uhx1665702664428.html", "html": "<html><body><header class=\"zDocsTopicPageHead\"><h1 class=\"css-g931ng\">Example: Using Database Data Paging</h1><div class=\"zDocsTopicActions\" role=\"list\"><div class=\"zDocsBundlePagination\" data-testid=\"next-prev-container\" role=\"listitem\"><div class=\"zDocsPrevTopicButton zDocsPrevTopicButton\"><span class=\"\"><a aria-label=\"Previous:   Data Paging in Web Applications \" class=\"\" data-tooltip-content=\"Previous:   Data Paging in Web Applications \" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" data-tooltip-open=\"false\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fwc1665702664241.html\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-prev\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-prev\"></use></svg></a></span></div><div class=\"zDocsNextTopicButton zDocsNextTopicButton\"><span class=\"\"><a aria-label=\"Next:   Example: Using Client State for Data Paging \" class=\"\" data-tooltip-content=\"Next:   Example: Using Client State for Data Paging \" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" data-tooltip-open=\"false\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tfk1665702664321.html\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></a></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsMyDocsMenu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Add to My Topics\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Add to My Topics\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" id=\"addToMyDocsDropdownTrigger\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-bookmark-add\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-bookmark-add\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-bookmark-add\"></use></svg>Add to My Topics</span><div aria-labelledby=\"pdfDropdown\" class=\"dropdown-menu dropdown-menu-right\"><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/uhx1665702664428.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub\">Add selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/uhx1665702664428.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub_head\">Add Topic &amp; Subtopics with topic head</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/uhx1665702664428.html?finish_action=mydocs_pub\">Add entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsWatchButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Watch\" class=\"d-lg-flex d-none zDocsSubscribeButton\" data-tooltip-content=\"Watch\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsSubscribeButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye zDocsSubscribeButton\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsSubscribeButton\">Watch</span></span></div><div class=\"zDocsExportPdfMenu zDocsExportMenu\" data-testid=\"export-pdf-menu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Download PDF\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Download PDF\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#ZdExportPDFModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3616302\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3616302\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 14, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104uhx1665702664428.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/uhx1665702664428.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/uhx1665702664428.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"uhx1665702664428\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Example: Using Database Data Paging\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__exampleusing_database_data_paging_77676\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">This examples demonstrates the use of the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">read</span> statement's <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">offset</span> option and other arguments to implement a data paging mechanism in a web application.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__p_d22343e1_d22344e1_d22345e1\">The example implements a data paging mechanism that allows the user to:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__li_d10877e1_d10878e1_d10879e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__p_d22346e1_d22347e1_d22348e1\">Navigate through the set of data using First, Previous, Next, and Last buttons.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__li_d10880e1_d10881e1_d10882e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__p_d22349e1_d22350e1_d22351e1\">Specify the page size (in the <code class=\"ph codeph\">PAGESIZE</code> field). The page size is used to calculate the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">offset</span>.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__p_d22352e1_d22353e1_d22354e1\">For simplicity, no user search profiles are included—the data is retrieved using the ID field (the primary key), and ordered by ID in ascending order.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__topic_d15852e1_d15853e1_d15854e1_d15855e1_d15856e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d789503e86\">\n                        \n Detail Triggers\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__p_d22358e1_d22359e1_d22360e1\">The detail trigger of each navigation button sets the value of the PAGENUM.CONTROL field and calls the <code class=\"ph codeph\">lpRetrieve</code> ProcScript module.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">trigger detail ; of button First\npublic web\nPAGENUM.CONTROL = 0 <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#uhx1665702664428__li_d10883e1_d10884e1_d10885e1\">1</a><a class=\"xref\" href=\"#uhx1665702664428__li_d10883e1_d10884e1_d10885e1\"></a><img alt=\"callout 1\" class=\"image\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__image_m5n_ywl_scc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/zzcallout1.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\ncall lpRetrieve\nend; detail\ntrigger detail ; of button Next\npublic web\nPAGENUM.CONTROL = PAGENUM.CONTROL+1 <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#uhx1665702664428__li_d10886e1_d10887e1_d10888e1\">2</a><a class=\"xref\" href=\"#uhx1665702664428__li_d10886e1_d10887e1_d10888e1\"></a><img alt=\"callout 2\" class=\"image\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__image_c5r_3xl_scc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/zzcallout2.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\ncall lpRetrieve\nend; detail\ntrigger detail ; of button Prev\npublic web\nPAGENUM.CONTROL = PAGENUM.CONTROL -1 <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#uhx1665702664428__li_d10889e1_d10890e1_d10891e1\">3</a><a class=\"xref\" href=\"#uhx1665702664428__li_d10889e1_d10890e1_d10891e1\"></a><img alt=\"callout3\" class=\"image\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__image_kw2_lxl_scc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/zzcallout3.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\ncall lpRetrieve\nend; detail\ntrigger detail ; button Last\npublic web\nPAGENUM.CONTROL = -1 <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#uhx1665702664428__li_d10892e1_d10893e1_d10894e1\">4</a><a class=\"xref\" href=\"#uhx1665702664428__li_d10892e1_d10893e1_d10894e1\"></a><img alt=\"callout4\" class=\"image\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__image_xf3_nxl_scc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/zzcallout4.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\nretrieve/e \"&lt;$entname&gt;\nend; detail</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__li_d10883e1_d10884e1_d10885e1\">For the FIRST button, the page number is set to 0\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__li_d10886e1_d10887e1_d10888e1\">For the NEXT button, the page number is incremented by 1\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__li_d10889e1_d10890e1_d10891e1\">For the PREV button, the page number is decreased by 1\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__li_d10892e1_d10893e1_d10894e1\">For the LAST button, the page number is set to -1. The total number of pages is unknown, so -1 indicates the last page.\n </li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__topic_d15857e1_d15858e1_d15859e1_d15860e1_d15861e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d789503e155\">\n                        \n lpRetrieve\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__p_d22364e1_d22365e1_d22366e1\">The <code class=\"ph codeph\">lpRetrieve</code> module centralizes the retrieve action for all buttons, and provides extra processing for the last page.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">function lRetrieve\nvariables\n numeric vTotalRec\nendvariables\n; If the last page is requested, calculate the page number\nif (PAGENUM.CONTROL = -1) <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#uhx1665702664428__li_d10895e1_d10896e1_d10897e1\">1</a><a class=\"xref\" href=\"#uhx1665702664428__li_d10895e1_d10896e1_d10897e1\"></a><img alt=\"callout1\" class=\"image\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__image_xwz_5xl_scc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/zzcallout1.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n ;Calculate the total number of pages \n selectdb count(ID) from \"&lt;$entname&gt;\" to vTotalRec <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#uhx1665702664428__li_d10898e1_d10899e1_d10900e1\">2</a><a class=\"xref\" href=\"#uhx1665702664428__li_d10898e1_d10899e1_d10900e1\"></a><img alt=\"callout2\" class=\"image\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__image_a4r_2yl_scc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/zzcallout2.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n vTotalRec = vTotalRec / PAGESIZE.CONTROL <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#uhx1665702664428__li_d10901e1_d10902e1_d10903e1\">3</a><a class=\"xref\" href=\"#uhx1665702664428__li_d10901e1_d10902e1_d10903e1\"></a><img alt=\"callout3\" class=\"image\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__image_umx_jyl_scc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/zzcallout3.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n ; Set the page number \n vTotalRec -= 1\n PAGENUM.CONTROL = vTotalRec[trunc]\nendif\n;retrieve the data, thereby executing the read trigger\nclear/e \"&lt;$entname&gt;\"\nretrieve/e \"&lt;$entname&gt;\" <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#uhx1665702664428__li_d10904e1_d10905e1_d10906e1\">4</a><a class=\"xref\" href=\"#uhx1665702664428__li_d10907e1_d10908e1_d10909e1\"></a><img alt=\"callout4\" class=\"image\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__image_sbn_myl_scc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/zzcallout4.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\nend ;lRetrieve</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__li_d10895e1_d10896e1_d10897e1\">If the last page has been requested (<code class=\"ph codeph\">$vPageNum$ = -1</code>), …\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__li_d10898e1_d10899e1_d10900e1\">… use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">selectdb</span> to count the number of records …\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__li_d10901e1_d10902e1_d10903e1\">… and calculate what the actual page number is. This is needed to go to the previous page. Rounding the number ensures that the number is an integer.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__li_d10904e1_d10905e1_d10906e1\">… but can result in a last page that is too high. If this is the case, decrease the page number by 1.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__li_d10907e1_d10908e1_d10909e1\">Retrieve the data, thereby firing the Read trigger of the entity.\n </li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__topic_d15862e1_d15863e1_d15864e1_d15865e1_d15866e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d789503e232\">\n                        \n Read trigger\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__p_d22370e1_d22371e1_d22372e1\">The entity's read trigger is fired by <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">retrieve</span> statement, located in the local ProcScript module <code class=\"ph codeph\">lpRetrieve</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">;READ trigger \nvariables\n numeric vOffset\nendvariables\n vOffset = $vPageNum$ * PAGESIZE.CONTROL <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#uhx1665702664428__li_d10910e1_d10911e1_d10912e1\">1</a><a class=\"xref\" href=\"#uhx1665702664428__li_d10910e1_d10911e1_d10912e1\"></a><img alt=\"callout1\" class=\"image\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__image_e5j_tyl_scc\" src=\"https://docs-be.rocketsoftware.com/bundle/uniface_104/page/zzcallout1.png?_LANG=enus\"/>\n read options \"maxhits=%%PAGESIZE.CONTROL%%%·;offset=%%vOffset%%%\" order by ID <a class=\"xref\" href=\"#uhx1665702664428__li_d10913e1_d10914e1_d10915e1\">2</a></code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<ol class=\"ol\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__li_d10910e1_d10911e1_d10912e1\">Calculate the required offset by multiplying the page number by the page size.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"uhx1665702664428__li_d10913e1_d10914e1_d10915e1\">Read the data, ordering it in ascending order by ID.\n </li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vvq1665702552959.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>read</a><p>Set the access mode.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/tfk1665702664321.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Example: Using Client State for Data Paging</a><p>This examples demonstrates one approach to implementing a data paging mechanism in a web application, when it is not possible to use the offset option of the read statement.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616302\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616302\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Example: Using Database Data Paging Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 14, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Example: Using Database Data Paging This examples demonstrates the use of the read statement's offset option and other arguments to implement a data paging mechanism in a web application. The example implements a data paging mechanism that allows the user to: Navigate through the set of data using First, Previous, Next, and Last buttons. Specify the page size (in the PAGESIZE field). The page size is used to calculate the offset . For simplicity, no user search profiles are included—the data is retrieved using the ID field (the primary key), and ordered by ID in ascending order. Detail Triggers The detail trigger of each navigation button sets the value of the PAGENUM.CONTROL field and calls the lpRetrieve ProcScript module. trigger detail ; of button First public web PAGENUM.CONTROL = 0 1 call lpRetrieve end; detail trigger detail ; of button Next public web PAGENUM.CONTROL = PAGENUM.CONTROL+1 2 call lpRetrieve end; detail trigger detail ; of button Prev public web PAGENUM.CONTROL = PAGENUM.CONTROL -1 3 call lpRetrieve end; detail trigger detail ; button Last public web PAGENUM.CONTROL = -1 4 retrieve/e \"<$entname> end; detail Copy For the FIRST button, the page number is set to 0 For the NEXT button, the page number is incremented by 1 For the PREV button, the page number is decreased by 1 For the LAST button, the page number is set to -1. The total number of pages is unknown, so -1 indicates the last page. lpRetrieve The lpRetrieve module centralizes the retrieve action for all buttons, and provides extra processing for the last page. function lRetrieve variables numeric vTotalRec endvariables ; If the last page is requested, calculate the page number if (PAGENUM.CONTROL = -1) 1 ;Calculate the total number of pages selectdb count(ID) from \"<$entname>\" to vTotalRec 2 vTotalRec = vTotalRec / PAGESIZE.CONTROL 3 ; Set the page number vTotalRec -= 1 PAGENUM.CONTROL = vTotalRec[trunc] endif ;retrieve the data, thereby executing the read trigger clear/e \"<$entname>\" retrieve/e \"<$entname>\" 4 end ;lRetrieve Copy If the last page has been requested ( $vPageNum$ = -1 ), … … use selectdb to count the number of records … … and calculate what the actual page number is. This is needed to go to the previous page. Rounding the number ensures that the number is an integer. … but can result in a last page that is too high. If this is the case, decrease the page number by 1. Retrieve the data, thereby firing the Read trigger of the entity. Read trigger The entity's read trigger is fired by retrieve statement, located in the local ProcScript module lpRetrieve . ;READ trigger variables numeric vOffset endvariables vOffset = $vPageNum$ * PAGESIZE.CONTROL 1 read options \"maxhits=%%PAGESIZE.CONTROL%%%·;offset=%%vOffset%%%\" order by ID 2 Copy Calculate the required offset by multiplying the page number by the page size. Read the data, ordering it in ascending order by ID. Related Links read Set the access mode. Example: Using Client State for Data Paging This examples demonstrates one approach to implementing a data paging mechanism in a web application, when it is not possible to use the offset option of the read statement. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}